# Brief Introduction:

Since I wanted to build an interactive dashboard and later, a journal style webpage, I wanted to 
take a dataset that was relatable to everyone and at the same time helped everyone as well. As a 
result, I chose the "Top 1000 Movies on IMDB" dataset.

Ocassionally, everyone loves to relax and either binge watch a series or watch a good movie. This
visualization helps the user decide between the kind of movie that he/she wants to watch. 

There are various attributes in the dataset which when analyzed and visualized can help the user
pick a movie to watch which is worth their time.

### Some attributes are: 

1. IMDB Rating
2. Director Name
3. Cast
4. Meta-score
5. Gross Revenue
6. Certificate
7. No. of votes

# Dashboard 1: Certificates of Movies and it's attibutes:  

[TableauEmbed link:"https://public.tableau.com/views/Visualization1_16517991222160/Dashboard1?:language=en-US&:display_count=n&:origin=viz_share_link" width:"165%" margin-left:"auto" margin-right:"auto" height:"835"/]

## Navigation through the dashboard: 


#### This dashboard consists of 3 visualizations:

1. An illustration to show Movie Name, Certificate and it's IMDB Rating
2. A visualization to show Certificate of movies and Average Meta-score
3. A graphical representation of Movie Name, Gross amount and certificate  


## How to navigate through the dashboard to explore the dataset: 

The dashboard conists of 3 visualizations with 2 being on top and one being on bottom. The user can scroll through the first visualization, that is the
visualization on the top left to view the Movie Name, Certificate and the IMDB Rating. If the user wants to know more about the movie in order to decide
whether or not the user wants to see it, the user can select or click on any one of the movie titles and then the other two will change accordingly.

This visulization also helps the user know certain facts about the movie like the meta score and the gross amount of the movie. I personally believe, these are a few
factors which may affect the decision of a user to watch a movie or not watch it.

The added interactivity completes the dashboard together, as the user is able to view the complete information with just one click.


