## How to navigate through the dashboard to explore the dataset: 

The final dashboard talks about the one of the most important factors which affect a viewers decision regarding the movie: THE CAST OF THE MOVIE.

The final dashboard which encompasses three visualizations, talks clearly about the cast of the movie, that is all the actors of the movie. Various movies like:
Avengers Endgame, Ocean's Eleven, Jumanji, etc. have a star studded cast due to which they are the fan favorites of millions of people from across the world.


The ability to visualize the actors and the pair of actors can tell the user information about the compatibility and pairing of actors and at the same
give information about the actor who has worked with various other actors as well. The information about the cast of the movie can reveal other information
like the certificate, in some cases the genre and storyline as well in case of Oceans series or Avengers or Justice League, etc. 


All the three dashboards provide complete interactivity experience for the user so that the user can utilize them to the maximum level and 
can extract as much information as the user wants.


# Contextual Visualizations:


## Visualization 1:

[img src:`"static/images/imdb1.png"`/]

### Explanation:

This visualization shows a bar chart that breaks down the average IMDb rating by movie genre. We can see that animated films received the highest average rating of 7.43, while horror films received the lowest average rating of 5.62. The frequency bar depicts the various colors for various numbers of movies. The frequency of movies increases when the color shifts to a lighter shade of blue. Thriller and Drama films have the most produced and rated films.

## Visualization 2:

[img src:`"static/images/imdb2.png"`/]

### Explanation:

A line chart illustrating the relation between Runtime and IMDb rating can be seen in this visualization. The largest surge in ratings and runtime can be seen between 150 and 250 minutes. Following that, the ratings and runtime both suddenly decrease to a 4 rating. The majority of users, it can be deduced, favor a duration of 150 to 250 minutes. This graphic can aid in further investigation.

## Visualization 3:

[img src:`"static/images/imdb3.png"`/]

### Explanation:

This graph depicts the link between the year a film was released and its average rating. The year range is from before 1920 to 2020, and the average rating ranges from 1 to 10. The movies bar shows the amount of movies rated by color, with yellow representing the most and purple representing the least. Prior to 1920, the number of films and their ratings were both minimal. The number of films produced rose after 1920. The average movie rating increased dramatically from 3.5 to 6.5 between 1920 and 2020.

